{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"head-husk-stead","description":"# Author the 3 eval specs + offline discipline tests (Phase 1)\n\n## What\n\nAuthor packaged specs mirroring the plan-review/code-quality pattern, using the\nschema + registry from the foundation task:\n- `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/completion-verifier.eval.yaml`\n- `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/ticket-quality.eval.yaml`\n- `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/spec-alignment.eval.yaml`\n\nEach: generator `anthropic:claude-opus-4-8`, epochs>=2, `at_least(k)`, coverage\nthreshold, >=1 deterministic gating scorer (registered), a report-only cross-family\njudge (GPT-4o, temp 0/seed/dated snapshot, gates:false), a balanced corpus-tagged\ndataset (finding/pass[/fail]) seeded from real cases (docs/experiments FP taxonomy +\nrebar's own tickets), and a non-empty gold_set.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] 3 specs exist under `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/`, each validate_eval_spec-clean.\n- [ ] Each spec's deterministic scorers are all registered (foundation task); judge is disciplined + gates:false.\n- [ ] Datasets are balanced, corpus-tagged, and seeded from real observed cases where available.\n- [ ] Offline unit tests assert per-spec: validity, non-empty gold_set, dataset balance, and registered scorers.\n- [ ] `eval-discipline` CI validates all 7 specs (the new 3 included) at zero API cost.","id":"c156-9e44-6a67-43d2","parent_id":"b4af-6782-0f12-4a1d","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Author 3 eval specs + offline discipline tests (Phase 1)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782578570751668001,"uuid":"2e8b123f-77a6-48d7-ab3b-029edb3a6533"}